Remote

1.Working with Remote Repositories

Q.Explain what remote repositories are.
Ans:Remote repositories are versions of your project hosted on the internet or another network, enabling collaboration and centralized storage.

Q.How to add, fetch, pull, and push to remotes.
Ans:Use `git remote add origin <url>`, `git fetch origin`, `git pull origin <branch>`, and `git push origin <branch>`.

Q.Assignment: Add a remote to your local repository and push your changes.
Ans:Add a remote with `git remote add origin <url>` and push changes with `git push -u origin <branch>`.
